Profitability status refers to whether a film's total sales are greater than its total budget; 
A film's total budget is the sum of production, marketing, post-production, visual effects, and casting costs;
Profit is calculated by subtracting total budget from total sales;
Profitability rank is determined by ordering films in descending order based on their profits.

